FBIS3-6797 "dreas055_d_94011" FBIS-EAS-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Mar 1994 South Korea DPRK Reportedly Warns U.S. on Demands SK2203025794 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 22 Mar 94 p 2 SK2203025794 Seoul CHOSON ILBO Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Text] It has been learned on 21 March that North Korea recently sent a letter to the U.S. Government through channels in New York warning that if the United States does not withdraw its demands for additional International Atomic Energy Agency inspections and the exchange of North and South Korean special envoys as the precondition of the third round of the North Korea- U.S. talks, North Korea could stop operating various surveillance equipment installed in Yongbyon's nuclear facilities.
